Package parkingRobot

Class INavigation.ParkingSlot

  • java.lang.Object
    • parkingRobot.INavigation.ParkingSlot
  • Enclosing interface:
    INavigation
    public static class INavigation.ParkingSlot
extends java.lang.Object
    represents one entry in the parking slot data bank. It contains all necessary information about one parking slot: - slot ID - slot status (whether it is/is not suitable for parking), - measured position of the slot begin front boundary, - measured position of the slot back boundary, - quality of parking slot measurement (die Güte der Parklückenvermessung).
    Author:
    IfA

    • Field Detail

      • ID

        int ID
        stores the parking slot ID. The ID is set for a new slot, added to the data bank, as the number of this new slot entry. When delegating the robot to a special parking slot a distinction between the stored slots is necessary and is given by this identification.

      • backBoundaryPosition

        lejos.geom.Point backBoundaryPosition
        position of parking slot back boundary, robot passes it first then the front boundary

      • frontBoundaryPosition

        lejos.geom.Point frontBoundaryPosition
        position of parking slot front boundary, robot passes it second after the back boundary

      • status

        private INavigation.ParkingSlot.ParkingSlotStatus status
        characterization of the parking slot measurement with the defined state value. Per default is the parking slot not suitable.

      • measurementQuality

        int measurementQuality
        stores the quality of parking slot measurement. Lower value assumes lower quality.
